sentences.english: I hope Your Most Reverend will take the lead and we shall do our best to follow in this work.

sentences.english: Assuming the High Septon had not put her to death by the time he got back to the city.
sentences.chinese: 姑且認爲當他回去的時候她還沒有死在大主教手裏。

sentences.english: Monastery which has a high level of schools and the Archbishop of schools.

sentences.english: The Archbishop of Canterbury is called the Primate of All England.
sentences.chinese: 坎特伯雷大主教被稱爲全英總主教。

sentences.english: Pope Benedict XVI arrives in London to meet the Archbishop of Canterbury Dr. Rowan Williams.
sentences.chinese: 教皇本篤十六世抵達倫敦會見坎特伯裏大主教威廉斯。

sentences.english: But Canterbury would always be the city of the archbishop and monks of Christ Church.
sentences.chinese: 然而，坎特伯雷素來是基督教大主教和僧侶的聚集地。

sentences.english: Negus and his patriarchs were in tears.

sentences.english: In a few hours time, the Church of England will enthrone its first black Archbishop.

sentences.english: It should be after the Archbishop of Canterbury pronounces them man and wife.

sentences.english: Archbishop Faol takes the remaining clerics with him and forms the Order of the Silver Hand.

坎特伯雷大主教柏克特T。

sentences.english: The Archbishop of York has condemned an anti-homosexuality bill going through parliament in Uganda.

sentences.english: Archbishop: The Maid wants to start fighting again.

sentences.english: Snub-nosed monkeys are among the most endangered primate species in Asia.

sentences.english: The prioress could do nothing; the archbishop had spoken.
